In MSTest v4, the `out` parameter overload of `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>` was removed. The method now **returns** the typed value directly.

**Fix:**

```csharp
// Before (v3)
Assert.IsInstanceOfType<MyType>(obj, out var typed);

// After (v4)
var typed = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<MyType>(obj);
```

Same assertion, same type check — just assign the return value instead of passing `out`. This applies everywhere you use the pattern; a simple find-and-replace across your test files should resolve all the CS1615 errors.
